# Laravel Backend Conventions

## Structure

- Controllers extend `BaseController`; respond with `$this->returnResponse($message, $data)`
  or `$this->returnError($message, $data, $httpCode)`. Never return raw arrays.
- Business logic lives in `app/Services/`; third-party integrations in `app/Adapters/`
  (e.g. `app/Adapters/Selcom/`). Controllers stay thin.
- External API configs go in `config/*.php` reading from `env()`. Never call `env()`
  outside config files.

## Migrations

- Guard against duplicate columns with `Schema::hasColumn()` when altering tables
  (production DB has drifted before — see `2023_10_13_193842_update_referral_agents.php`).
- All new columns nullable or with defaults; production data already exists.

## Seeders

- Seeders run on EVERY container boot (`entrypoint.sh` runs `db:seed || true`).
  They MUST be idempotent: use `firstOrCreate`/`updateOrCreate`, never bare `create`.
  Spatie permissions: wrap in existence checks (PermissionAlreadyExists crashes boot).

## Logging

- Log with context; a request-id is auto-attached by `RequestReferenceMiddleware`.
- Never log Selcom API secrets, full card data, or APP_KEY.

## PHP runtime

- Production container serves via `php -S 0.0.0.0:8000 -t public public/index.php`
  (NOT `artisan serve` — it returned 500s behind the nginx proxy). Don't change this
  in `docker/php/entrypoint.sh` without testing through nginx.
